# FID — source of truth

All FID application work and write-ups must align with the guidelines, objectives, and eligibility criteria detailed at: https://opportunitiesforyouth.org/2026/06/12/fid-call-for-proposals-2026-apply-for-up-to-e4-million-to-scale-innovative-solutions-tackling-poverty-and-inequality-worldwide/

- Ensure proposals explicitly address the FID focus areas: scalable solutions for poverty and inequality reduction, innovation potential, and measurable impact.
- Submissions should meet all stated requirements for format, track, documentation, and organisational eligibility as listed on the call for proposals.
- Reference the original FID documentation for definitions of innovation, scale, and impact; if requirements differ from internal conventions, prioritise the FID source.
- Cite the above link for any claims or descriptions related to the call; avoid paraphrasing that risks deviating from the original intent and priorities.
- Before finalising or publishing any work, cross-check against the live FID guidelines to ensure continued compliance.

